JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s trade surplus grew to R9.49 billion ($727 million) in May following a revised R4.97 billion surplus in April, data from the revenue agency showed on Friday.Exports rose 15.4% to R105 billion on a month-on-month basis in May, while imports were up 11% to R95.5 billion , the South African Revenue Service said in a statement. ($1 = R13.0550) 